This paper deals with the problem of minimizing network delays, which is a fundamental problem in computer networks and communication systems. The paper proposes scalable and data-driven approaches for this problem, which suggests that it belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic approximation and sampling techniques, which are commonly used in Statistical Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also deals with optimization and design problems, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of delay distributions, which is relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
